The robot stars in Star Wars: The Force Awakens . 
  JJ Abrams confirmed that a real robot was used during filming but did not reveal how it works . 
  BB-8 took to the stage at Star Wars Celebration convention in Anaheim, California . 
  It ran rings around retro droid R2-D2 on its spherical body . 
  The droid’s body is a spherical ball that can move in any direction . 
  But it also has a free-moving head that doesn’t fall off . 
 